[SN]TITLE[SN]
Tesco 'Black Friday' disorder: Three charged

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Three men have been charged after "Black Friday" sales resulted in disorder at seven Tesco stores in Greater Manchester.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The charges relate to incidents at supermarkets in Burnage, Hattersley and Irlam on 28 November.
A 42-year-old man from Manchester and a 28-year-old man from Pendleton have been accused of assault by beating.
A man aged 45, from Hyde, has been charged with a public order offence for using threatening or abusive language.
The three men will appear before Manchester and Tameside magistrates between 10 December to 15 December.
